WHERE

The WHERE clause allows you to specify a search condition for the rowsreturned by a query.


SELECT
    select_list
FROM
    table_name
WHERE
    search_condition;


FROM SELECT WHERE ORDERBY




# Using WHERE clause

SELECT 
    lastname, 
    firstname, 
    jobtitle
FROM
    employees
WHERE
    jobtitle = 'Sales Rep';



It finds all employees whose job titles are Sales Rep: